The paper deals with the problem of network intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a hybrid system that uses an artificial immune system and a self-organizing map, which involves techniques from neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the clustering of network connections, which is a common topic in the field of computational intelligence and soft computing (cs.SI).
